The paper deals with linear network coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on multicast networks, which are a type of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the complexity tradeoff between encoding and decoding, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of circular-shift operations is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the solvability behavior of randomly constructed codes, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
